            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> @lewis6991 interesting. From a philosophical perspective, I wouldn't consider hunks as diagnostics per se (in the sense that they don't represent issues or potential issues in code/files in the same way as spelling errors do).\r\n\r\nTo me, hunks are something that the user has to address as they make the file \"dirty\", just like how untouched files (usually) don't have any lint/lsp warnings. Diagnostics already include `INFO` and `HINT` which are not errors or necessarily issues.\r\n\r\nAt the very least, hunks question the scope of diagnostics. They either sit just within or just outside. I think spelling errors definitely sit inside but don't fall into any of the existing severities (Error, warning, info, hint) which are inherited from the LSP spec.",
