            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Fair enough, that's a logical viewpoint, and agree it makes sense. For me, they are slightly different only because the diagnostics are the things I resolve (creating 'dirty' hunks along the way) to get into the position where I then commit my changes. Matter of perspective I guess.\r\n\r\nDefinitely wouldn't be a practical issue to rework them as diagnostics I think as long as they lived in their own namespaces so could be \"ignored\" by diagnostic-processing keybindings/functions if the user wished (which thinking about it might require a 'namespace denylist' on e.g. `vim.diagnostic.next()`.",
